1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:31,150 --> 00:01:35,150
[Gank Your Heart]

3
00:01:35,729 --> 00:01:38,450
[Episode 18]

4
00:01:40,860 --> 00:01:42,270
Brother Xuan, you're back.

5
00:01:44,140 --> 00:01:45,530
Why did you bring me back?

6
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:48,500
Everyone's here.

7
00:01:48,960 --> 00:01:50,060
Let's start training.

8
00:01:51,350 --> 00:01:53,530
Captain went to Chairman Ji
and vouched for you,

9
00:01:53,670 --> 00:01:55,600
or Zhao Yang wouldn't have let it slide.

10
00:01:55,820 --> 00:01:58,590
Now that you're back,
you've got to control your temper.

11
00:01:58,770 --> 00:02:00,220
Stop causing trouble.

12
00:02:00,490 --> 00:02:01,710
Pei Xi.

13
00:02:02,160 --> 00:02:05,280
Don't think I'll thank you for that.
I won't.

14
00:02:05,550 --> 00:02:06,660
Lin Yi Xuan.

15
00:02:06,910 --> 00:02:08,139
Get back to training.

16
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:11,970
Come on. Let's start training.

17
00:02:22,620 --> 00:02:24,800
It's a training match with Newland.

18
00:02:25,390 --> 00:02:27,110
We must take it seriously.

19
00:02:28,030 --> 00:02:29,390
Four protect one.

20
00:02:29,570 --> 00:02:31,200
It won't make a difference.

21
00:02:31,370 --> 00:02:33,020
Stop wasting time. Hurry up.

22
00:02:53,140 --> 00:02:54,590
What are you doing here?

23
00:02:54,910 --> 00:02:56,450
I've been here for a long time.

24
00:02:56,579 --> 00:02:59,750
How can you not notice a handsome guy
like me? You're so hardworking.

25
00:02:59,970 --> 00:03:01,440
I'm not smart.

26
00:03:01,640 --> 00:03:04,020
I was engrossed in studying the questions.

27
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:06,840
How did you know I'm here?

28
00:03:07,630 --> 00:03:10,270
You weren't at Dream Traveler.
So I figured you'd be here.

29
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:12,160
And I was right.

30
00:03:13,050 --> 00:03:16,690
Your eyebrows are ending up in a knot.
What's wrong?

31
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:22,220
I asked to be Luo Tian's apprentice.

32
00:03:24,170 --> 00:03:26,750
But I was rejected.

33
00:03:27,030 --> 00:03:29,890
Hang on. You asked him directly?

34
00:03:31,170 --> 00:03:32,750
You're so bold.

35
00:03:32,930 --> 00:03:36,790
Ask Brother Summer if Mr. Luo
has had any apprentices in recent years.

36
00:03:37,060 --> 00:03:38,380
I know.

37
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:40,060
But Brother Summer said

38
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:44,550
that if Mr. Luo lectured me,
it means he thinks I have potential.

39
00:03:44,760 --> 00:03:46,820
That's why he was strict with me.

40
00:03:47,970 --> 00:03:50,890
You believe what Brother Summer said?

41
00:03:52,020 --> 00:03:54,750
He is Mr. Luo's best friend
for many years.

42
00:03:54,930 --> 00:03:56,600
I think he's right.

43
00:04:04,690 --> 00:04:07,510
Was he just trying to comfort me?

44
00:04:12,170 --> 00:04:14,120
Perhaps I'm hopeless.

45
00:04:16,350 --> 00:04:20,910
I shouldn't have listened to you and
chose to be a professional commentator.

46
00:04:22,170 --> 00:04:25,330
Does a decision let you achieve your goals
without putting in the effort?

47
00:04:25,420 --> 00:04:26,390
Besides,

48
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:29,820
are you going to stop working hard
just because Mr. Luo turned you down?

49
00:04:30,350 --> 00:04:33,840
Your goal is to be a commentator,
not someone's apprentice.

50
00:04:34,090 --> 00:04:36,900
If you win the Rising Star competition,

51
00:04:37,210 --> 00:04:40,530
then you'll be on the path
to becoming a commentator.

52
00:04:41,130 --> 00:04:42,670
You are right.

53
00:04:43,370 --> 00:04:45,880
But I think I am a little thickheaded.

54
00:04:46,710 --> 00:04:50,190
I've gone through
all the questions I can find.

55
00:04:50,630 --> 00:04:52,430
But I can only answer the questions.

56
00:04:52,610 --> 00:04:54,850
I can't grasp the feeling of
being a commentator.

57
00:04:56,290 --> 00:04:58,200
Remember I told you to play Yun Ti?

58
00:04:58,770 --> 00:05:02,200
Getting into the real game
is the fastest way to improve.

59
00:05:02,330 --> 00:05:03,430
Just like Mr. Luo.

60
00:05:03,610 --> 00:05:06,800
He used to be a professional gamer,
then he became a top commentator.

61
00:05:06,910 --> 00:05:08,860
He went through lots of practice.

62
00:05:09,060 --> 00:05:11,450
That's far more effective than memorizing.

63
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:20,330
What you're saying is,

64
00:05:20,860 --> 00:05:25,440
I should do a review on a match
and ask for advice?

65
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:28,600
I'm saying that you should go straight
to Mr. Luo after that.

66
00:05:28,950 --> 00:05:32,640
Worst case scenario, you get rejected.
But what if he's willing to guide you?

67
00:05:33,880 --> 00:05:35,050
You're right.

68
00:05:36,180 --> 00:05:38,240
You're amazing, Ji Xiang Kong.

69
00:05:38,540 --> 00:05:41,460
There are a lot of people here.
Please calm down.

70
00:05:41,710 --> 00:05:43,470
Stop making rumors spread.

71
00:05:44,570 --> 00:05:46,420
I was overjoyed.

72
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:48,370
Thank you.

73
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:52,180
Come on, we're friends.
No need to thank me.

74
00:05:52,890 --> 00:05:56,230
Okay. I have to get back and rest
after enjoying this milk tea.

75
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:18,320
Lin Yi Xuan, stop losing points.

76
00:06:18,710 --> 00:06:20,300
I did it on purpose.

77
00:06:20,610 --> 00:06:23,070
Lin Yi Xuan, don't tower dive.

78
00:06:23,250 --> 00:06:25,180
I'm about to collapse here at the back.

79
00:06:25,270 --> 00:06:26,590
I got it.

80
00:06:27,910 --> 00:06:30,550
Brother Xuan, support the ADC.

81
00:06:30,680 --> 00:06:32,350
I'm out of money. Do it yourself.

82
00:06:35,010 --> 00:06:37,230
Wait for me. Wait up.

83
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:41,070
I'm 100 points behind my opponent.
How am I supposed to fight?

84
00:06:52,550 --> 00:06:53,830
Is this all you've got?

85
00:06:54,090 --> 00:06:57,740
Yes, that's right. Put me back
in the reserve team if you don't like it.

86
00:06:59,370 --> 00:07:02,050
So this is the best Support
that Ji Xiang Kong mentioned?

87
00:07:02,850 --> 00:07:04,470
Even a new player performs better.

88
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:08,740
What do you mean?

89
00:07:08,960 --> 00:07:10,610
Brother Kong talked to you?

90
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:16,310
Hey, I'm talking to you.

91
00:07:20,310 --> 00:07:22,130
Brother Kong talked to him?

92
00:07:27,350 --> 00:07:28,890
He went to see Brother Kong?

93
00:07:29,020 --> 00:07:30,080
I don't know.

94
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:45,260
Why are you just standing there?

95
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:46,990
Let's begin.

96
00:07:48,740 --> 00:07:50,740
I seriously don't know what you want.

97
00:07:51,159 --> 00:07:53,900
What I want? Can't you play basketball?

98
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:55,710
That's impossible.

99
00:07:55,950 --> 00:07:58,330
According to your file,
you are good at basketball.

100
00:08:00,090 --> 00:08:01,630
That was before.

101
00:08:03,650 --> 00:08:05,970
Three years ago, a Mid in Newland.

102
00:08:06,470 --> 00:08:07,880
You had quite a good record.

103
00:08:09,770 --> 00:08:10,960
So?

104
00:08:12,010 --> 00:08:14,170
I don't believe
that you don't want to go back.

105
00:08:15,440 --> 00:08:16,630
I don't want to.

106
00:08:22,620 --> 00:08:24,550
You want to become a loser forever?

107
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:29,260
I've watched your matches.

108
00:08:37,270 --> 00:08:41,490
When you tower dived,
my coach told me you're a scary beast.

109
00:08:42,059 --> 00:08:44,920
But I can only think of one thing
looking at you now.

110
00:08:46,290 --> 00:08:47,740
You've lost your spirit.

111
00:08:50,650 --> 00:08:53,850
I don't understand
what Ji Xiang Kong is trying to do.

112
00:08:54,430 --> 00:08:56,190
It's good to have ideas.

113
00:08:56,930 --> 00:08:59,710
But playing basketball and E-sports
are completely different.

114
00:08:59,790 --> 00:09:02,920
He's taking up training time
to play basketball. This is ridiculous!

115
00:09:04,110 --> 00:09:05,160
Li Gan.

116
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:08,590
I only knew Lu Sheng likes playing safe.

117
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:12,330
But if he didn't reject
playing Mid this time,

118
00:09:12,860 --> 00:09:15,600
I wouldn't have realized
that he has come to this state.

119
00:09:15,850 --> 00:09:18,670
Not aiming for achievements,
just avoiding mistakes.

120
00:09:19,420 --> 00:09:21,440
He has practically lost
his fighting spirit.

121
00:09:23,160 --> 00:09:25,890
Lu Sheng has a balanced record.

122
00:09:26,110 --> 00:09:27,430
He has a stable performance.

123
00:09:27,730 --> 00:09:29,360
I don't think he has a problem.

124
00:09:31,650 --> 00:09:33,560
Don't you think he is too stable?

125
00:09:34,070 --> 00:09:36,620
He keeps defending
and never attacks first.

126
00:09:36,930 --> 00:09:39,170
He even refuses to do anything risky.

127
00:09:50,970 --> 00:09:56,070
Perhaps Ji Xiang Kong is using his way
to revive Lu Sheng's fighting spirit.

128
00:09:56,380 --> 00:10:00,690
Even so, it's not something that can be
solved with a few rounds of basketball.

129
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:05,960
You and Ji Xiang Kong are still holding
onto the idea of letting Lu Sheng be Mid?

130
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:09,880
Should I give up the idea?

131
00:10:31,940 --> 00:10:33,950
What are you doing here
if you are not training?

132
00:10:35,890 --> 00:10:37,480
Why do you look so sad?

133
00:10:37,690 --> 00:10:38,950
Brother Kong.

134
00:10:41,040 --> 00:10:42,580
Did you

135
00:10:44,510 --> 00:10:46,350
ask Pei Xi to put me back on the team?

136
00:10:47,450 --> 00:10:50,540
Since you're back, you should train hard.
Why bother asking that?

137
00:10:50,940 --> 00:10:54,920
Why did you do that?

138
00:10:55,160 --> 00:10:57,620
He got rid of you as the captain.

139
00:10:57,710 --> 00:11:00,130
You know I don't agree with him.
Why did you beg him?

140
00:11:00,220 --> 00:11:02,330
I'm not going back.
I don't want his kindness.

141
00:11:02,900 --> 00:11:04,550
Why are you like this?

142
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:06,230
Where else can you go?

143
00:11:06,340 --> 00:11:10,160
Which team would want a player like you
who doesn't have team spirit?

144
00:11:10,340 --> 00:11:11,750
I can go anywhere.

145
00:11:12,190 --> 00:11:14,650
I can be a network manager
and train at Brother Sun's.

146
00:11:14,780 --> 00:11:17,070
It's better than staying with
the current Legends.

147
00:11:18,260 --> 00:11:19,310
-You sure?
-Yes.

148
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:21,070
You're leaving behind your teammates?

149
00:11:21,950 --> 00:11:23,090
Yes.

150
00:11:24,330 --> 00:11:26,350
-Come on.
-Where are we going?

151
00:11:26,530 --> 00:11:29,260
-Let's go cancel your contract.
-No, hang on. Let's talk.

152
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:30,580
What's the rush?

153
00:11:30,750 --> 00:11:32,700
You said it earlier. You can't backpedal.

154
00:11:32,950 --> 00:11:35,460
Good going. From now on, you're the boss.

155
00:11:35,640 --> 00:11:39,470
Canceling a two-year contract without
blinking an eye about the penalty fee.

156
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:42,150
I don't have money.
If I did, I would have left already.

157
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:44,130
I do. I'll sell my bike. Come on.

158
00:11:44,350 --> 00:11:45,270
Wait. Hang on.

159
00:11:45,410 --> 00:11:46,550
-Stop, stop!
-Come on.

160
00:11:46,680 --> 00:11:47,870
Come back.

161
00:11:49,150 --> 00:11:51,070
I was wrong. Happy now?

162
00:11:52,930 --> 00:11:54,410
But let me set this straight.

163
00:11:54,650 --> 00:11:56,200
I'm not doing it for Pei Xi.

164
00:11:57,370 --> 00:11:58,790
I'm only doing it for you.

165
00:12:01,030 --> 00:12:03,090
Okay. Go back then.

166
00:12:04,280 --> 00:12:06,470
I still have time. Let's chat for a bit.

167
00:12:06,750 --> 00:12:09,830
-Buy me a meal if you're staying.
-Bye, Brother Kong.

168
00:12:20,320 --> 00:12:22,980
Thank you for watching. Bye!

169
00:12:29,710 --> 00:12:35,430
You've recorded tons of reviews
since this morning.

170
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:36,870
How was it this time?

171
00:12:36,970 --> 00:12:39,300
This is the best one so far.

172
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:42,600
But I still think it's awful.

173
00:12:42,780 --> 00:12:45,070
I feel embarrassed
showing this to Mr. Luo.

174
00:12:46,870 --> 00:12:49,910
Everything comes in order.

175
00:12:50,260 --> 00:12:52,900
Be brave. Show this to Luo Tian.

176
00:12:53,030 --> 00:12:55,140
That way you can improve. Right?

177
00:12:56,460 --> 00:12:57,390
Good point.

178
00:12:57,510 --> 00:12:59,850
This one it is. Let me make a copy.

179
00:13:03,280 --> 00:13:07,070
By the way, when was the last time
you talked to Yan Yan?

180
00:13:07,420 --> 00:13:08,390
Yan Yan?

181
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:10,930
It's been a few months.

182
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:14,860
She stayed at my place for a night
after quarreling with her boyfriend.

183
00:13:15,030 --> 00:13:18,380
I called her after that,
but she said she was busy.

184
00:13:19,430 --> 00:13:21,190
Why are you suddenly asking about her?

185
00:13:21,980 --> 00:13:24,440
It's nothing. I was just curious.

186
00:13:27,270 --> 00:13:29,250
Alright. I have to go.

187
00:13:29,860 --> 00:13:32,150
I have to quickly
bring this video to Mr. Luo.

188
00:13:32,320 --> 00:13:33,860
There's no need to rush.

189
00:13:34,350 --> 00:13:35,840
Strike while the iron is hot.

190
00:13:35,980 --> 00:13:37,360
Tidy things up for me.

191
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:40,820
Take an umbrella with you.
It looks cloudy outside.

192
00:14:05,550 --> 00:14:08,010
I can only succeed if I am bold enough.

193
00:14:13,650 --> 00:14:15,100
Sorry. I'm so sorry.

194
00:14:22,910 --> 00:14:24,690
-Mr. Luo.
-What are you doing here?

195
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:27,980
This is my commentary video.
Please take a look at it.

196
00:14:29,170 --> 00:14:31,060
Go get your umbrella. Go home.

197
00:14:31,190 --> 00:14:32,510
Thank you, Mr. Luo.

198
00:14:32,650 --> 00:14:34,530
-Go on.
-Bye, Mr. Luo!

199
00:14:43,070 --> 00:14:44,690
Bye, Mr. Luo!

200
00:14:45,800 --> 00:14:46,990
Great!

201
00:14:57,020 --> 00:14:59,120
Look what you did to yourself.

202
00:15:00,360 --> 00:15:02,480
Here. Drink this.

203
00:15:03,760 --> 00:15:05,270
Careful. It's hot.

204
00:15:05,900 --> 00:15:07,480
I've got to give it to you.

205
00:15:07,670 --> 00:15:09,470
You really thought you're invincible?

206
00:15:09,600 --> 00:15:12,600
You haven't slept all night
and stood in the rain for hours.

207
00:15:12,730 --> 00:15:14,660
You should look after yourself.

208
00:15:15,320 --> 00:15:17,670
I didn't expect it to rain so heavily.

209
00:15:18,100 --> 00:15:19,450
Careful. It's hot.

210
00:15:22,230 --> 00:15:23,560
Yi Yi.

211
00:15:23,680 --> 00:15:25,380
How much ginger did you use?

212
00:15:26,190 --> 00:15:28,670
More ginger will help you recover faster.

213
00:15:28,920 --> 00:15:32,350
Go to bed
as soon as you're done drinking this.

214
00:15:33,280 --> 00:15:34,990
I can't sleep now.

215
00:15:35,700 --> 00:15:37,940
Mr. Luo has probably
gotten off from work by now.

216
00:15:38,120 --> 00:15:39,830
He could have watched my video.

217
00:15:40,930 --> 00:15:43,240
Yi Yi, I'm so nervous right now.

218
00:15:44,540 --> 00:15:45,960
Relax.

219
00:15:46,170 --> 00:15:49,160
Why don't you give him a call?

220
00:15:49,740 --> 00:15:51,670
I'm not doing it. I'm scared.

221
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:54,700
What are you afraid of?

222
00:15:54,920 --> 00:15:57,780
I went through hoops
to get his phone number for you.

223
00:15:57,870 --> 00:16:00,070
Now you're telling me
you're afraid to call him?

224
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:02,840
If I were you,
I would have called him right away.

225
00:16:02,980 --> 00:16:04,850
I would keep pestering him.

226
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:06,540
There's nothing to be afraid of.

227
00:16:06,980 --> 00:16:08,650
[Hello?]

228
00:16:10,370 --> 00:16:12,480
[Hello? Hello?]

229
00:16:18,370 --> 00:16:19,850
Hello, Mr. Luo.

230
00:16:20,090 --> 00:16:21,500
[Yes. Hello?]

231
00:16:22,030 --> 00:16:24,530
Hello. I'm Qiu Ying.

232
00:16:24,890 --> 00:16:26,120
[Hello.]

233
00:16:26,470 --> 00:16:29,550
Have you seen the video I gave you?

234
00:16:29,770 --> 00:16:31,390
[Your USB isn't working.]

235
00:16:31,660 --> 00:16:33,110
What?

236
00:16:34,920 --> 00:16:38,480
It's probably because of the rain.
I'm so sorry, Mr. Luo.

237
00:16:38,570 --> 00:16:40,640
I'll make a new copy
and bring it to you now.

238
00:16:40,770 --> 00:16:42,040
I'm sorry.

239
00:16:42,180 --> 00:16:43,540
[You've lost your chance.]

240
00:16:43,670 --> 00:16:44,960
Hello, Mr. Luo?

241
00:16:46,270 --> 00:16:47,650
He hung up?

242
00:16:49,310 --> 00:16:52,500
How could you break your USB?

243
00:16:53,240 --> 00:16:56,020
It dropped into a puddle
because of the rain.

244
00:16:56,300 --> 00:16:57,800
What?

245
00:17:01,100 --> 00:17:02,890
I'm such an idiot.

246
00:17:03,170 --> 00:17:04,440
Forget it.

247
00:17:04,750 --> 00:17:06,109
Don't be so sad over it.

248
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:10,430
But isn't Luo Tian being too mean?

249
00:17:10,650 --> 00:17:12,190
You didn't do it on purpose.

250
00:17:12,490 --> 00:17:15,010
The world can still go round without him.

251
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:18,790
Trust me. One day, you'll show him

252
00:17:18,920 --> 00:17:21,470
how amazing you are
when you're on the commentary stage.

253
00:17:21,599 --> 00:17:23,490
Make him regret.

254
00:17:25,339 --> 00:17:27,380
"Show him".

255
00:17:28,990 --> 00:17:31,860
Yi Yi, hurry. Bring me your USB.

256
00:17:32,510 --> 00:17:33,480
What for?

257
00:17:34,140 --> 00:17:35,900
He's doing a review tomorrow.

258
00:17:36,520 --> 00:17:39,770
I don't care if he'll give me a chance.
I must show him.

259
00:17:42,980 --> 00:17:45,320
Go on. Hurry up. Go get it.

260
00:17:45,490 --> 00:17:48,000
